---
{
	layout: "layouts/base"
}
---

<section id="intro">
	<div class="content">
		<div class="who-am-i">
			<h1 class="main-heading">I'm <em>Aubrey</em></h1>
			<img src="/assets/img/aubrey.jpg" alt="Aubrey Portwood">
		</div>

		<div class="heres-the-deal">
			<div class="content">
				{% set content %}
				I build and maintain websites for businesses who are **sick of DIY** and want their website to **get out of the way!**

				Hire a web developer _(me)_ who works directly with you **and takes care of everything.**
				{% endset %}
				{{ content | replace ( "\t", '' ) | markdown | safe }}
			</div>
		</div>

		<div class="you-run-your-business">
			<p><strong>You run your business.</strong></p>
			<p>I run the website.</p>
		</div>
	</div>
</section>

<section id="how">
	<div class="content">

		<h2>How it works</h2>

		<h3>We build your website.</h3>

		<div class="content">
			{{ "Unless you already have a website, **we build a website that's directly aligned with your business's goals.**" | markdown | safe }}
			{{ "They're **lean**, **simple**, and **you own it.** End our relationship? **Your website stays up.**" | markdown | safe }}
		</div>

		<h3>Now I'm on your team.</h3>

		<div class="content">
			{{ "**Need content updates?** Want to run a campaign? Not sure what to do next? **I work directly with you every month** to get the most out of your website. Whatever's going on, I make sure your website is working along-side your what your business is doing." | markdown | safe }}
			{{ "**Think of me as a member of your team going forward.** Expect me to keep up with things going on in your business and keeping your website up to date." | markdown | safe }}
		</div>
	</div>
</section>

